
[1]chore

   CHORE, n. In America, this word denotes small work of a domestic kind,
   as distinguished from the principal work of the day. It is generally
   used in the plural, chores, which includes the daily or occasional
   business of feeding cattle and other animals, preparing fuel, sweeping
   the house, cleaning furniture, &c. [See Char.]
